[{"id":"VR871930","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which figure shows a correct representation for the magnetic field, and why?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR871930_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> show representations of the magnetic field around a bar magnet.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a magnetic field around a bar magnet in two representations labeled Figure 1 and Figure 2. In each figure, the bar magnet is oriented horizontally with its north pole to the left and its south pole to the right. Figure 1 shows a horizontal field line pointing toward the south pole, a horizontal field line pointing away from the north pole, and closed loops around the top and bottom of the magnet pointing away from the north pole and toward the south pole. Figure 2 shows straight field lines arrayed around the two poles pointing toward the north pole and away from the south pole.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871930.g05.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, because magnetic field lines form closed loops that point away from the north pole and towards the south pole outside the magnet</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, because magnetic field lines originate on the north pole of the magnet and terminate on the south pole of the magnet</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, because the magnetic field lines from a bar magnet are straight lines</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, because the magnetic field lines at the ends of the magnets are parallel to each other</p>"],"answer":0}]